1
00:00:00,919 --> 00:00:03,130
The US and China are in a trade war.

2
00:00:03,130 --> 00:00:04,870
And wars need weapons.

3
00:00:04,870 --> 00:00:08,950
And what better weapon to strike hard at the
US imperialists...

4
00:00:08,950 --> 00:00:10,280
than with your own currency!

5
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:12,680
Surely, nothing could go wrong!

6
00:00:17,240 --> 00:00:18,199
Welcome back to China Uncensored.

7
00:00:18,199 --> 00:00:19,750
I’m Chris Chappell.

8
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:21,400
Just when you thought the US-China trade war

9
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:24,480
was chugging along just fine already,

10
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:26,869
President Trump decided to up the ante.

11
00:00:26,869 --> 00:00:28,840
The Trump administration has announced the
US

12
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:30,220
will put tariffs on nearly

13
00:00:30,220 --> 00:00:33,370
$300 billion dollars worth of Chinese imports—

14
00:00:33,370 --> 00:00:36,499
pretty much everything that doesn’t have
a tariff already.

15
00:00:36,499 --> 00:00:37,539
Some of those tariffs are slated

16
00:00:37,539 --> 00:00:40,170
to go into effect on September 1st, others—

17
00:00:40,170 --> 00:00:41,300
as announced yesterday—

18
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:43,920
would go into effect on December 15th.

19
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:47,449
So in the face of this American superpower...

20
00:00:47,449 --> 00:00:50,639
what can the poor, oppressed Chinese leaders
do?

21
00:00:50,639 --> 00:00:53,699
One answer could be... weaponize their currency!

22
00:00:53,699 --> 00:00:56,929
Thanks to the enormous power of the Chinese
Communist Party

23
00:00:56,929 --> 00:01:00,340
over the government, the banks, and state-run
industries,

24
00:01:00,340 --> 00:01:04,769
it has a lot of control over the currency
and how goods are priced.

25
00:01:04,769 --> 00:01:08,340
The Chinese central bank has recently allowed
the Chinese currency—

26
00:01:08,340 --> 00:01:11,820
the yuan—to get weaker against the US dollar.

27
00:01:11,820 --> 00:01:15,380
That means Chinese exports to the US are cheaper.

28
00:01:15,380 --> 00:01:17,880
And that counteracts some of Trump’s tariffs

29
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:20,799
that make those same exports more expensive.

30
00:01:20,799 --> 00:01:22,130
It balances out.

31
00:01:22,130 --> 00:01:23,130
So in a way,

32
00:01:23,130 --> 00:01:26,130
that’s like using the currency as a defensive
weapon.

33
00:01:26,130 --> 00:01:29,829
And a weaker yuan also hurts American companies

34
00:01:29,829 --> 00:01:32,119
doing business inside China.

35
00:01:32,119 --> 00:01:35,729
Those Chevys sold in Shanghai just got more
expensive.

36
00:01:35,729 --> 00:01:38,369
Why not buy a Chinese car instead?

37
00:01:38,369 --> 00:01:41,340
So that’s China using currency as an offensive
weapon,

38
00:01:41,340 --> 00:01:43,520
to hurt US companies.

39
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:46,350
And it’s not just currency that can be a
weapon.

40
00:01:46,350 --> 00:01:48,590
In response to the latest tariffs,

41
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:51,729
the Chinese regime has already ordered state-run
companies

42
00:01:51,729 --> 00:01:54,609
to stop buying American crops, like soybeans.

43
00:01:54,609 --> 00:01:58,359
That’s a weapon designed to hurt US farmers—

44
00:01:58,359 --> 00:02:01,240
and with that, hurt Donald Trump’s voter
base.

45
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:04,189
And if going after US farmers isn’t enough,

46
00:02:04,189 --> 00:02:06,539
China’s producers of rare earth metals say

47
00:02:06,539 --> 00:02:09,560
they’re ready to weaponize their supply
stranglehold.

48
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,989
It’s a stranglehold because China controls

49
00:02:11,989 --> 00:02:15,520
about 80% of the world’s rare earth metals.

50
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:18,900
That includes elements like yttrium and neodymium

51
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:22,200
that are essential for iPhones and other electronics.

52
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:25,020
Of course, if iPhones become too expensive,

53
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,459
you’ll have no choice but to buy alternatives,

54
00:02:27,459 --> 00:02:29,410
like the Huawei P20 Pro!

55
00:02:29,410 --> 00:02:33,269
It has all the features you crave in a knockoff
iPhone,

56
00:02:33,269 --> 00:02:35,110
with none of the security protections!

57
00:02:35,110 --> 00:02:38,060
Of course, there’s a potential problem

58
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:39,310
with the Chinese Communist Party

59
00:02:39,310 --> 00:02:43,269
weaponizing the Chinese currency and other
parts of the economy:

60
00:02:43,269 --> 00:02:48,269
The bigger the weapon, the bigger the recoil.

61
00:02:48,269 --> 00:02:50,450
If the Communist Party restricts exports

62
00:02:50,450 --> 00:02:52,260
of rare earth metals to the US,

63
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:56,299
US companies may simply increase their own
production—

64
00:02:56,299 --> 00:03:00,290
because local mining becomes more profitable
when import prices go up.

65
00:03:00,290 --> 00:03:03,049
In fact, that happened with Japan.

66
00:03:03,049 --> 00:03:06,049
“China banned [rare earth] exports to Japan

67
00:03:06,049 --> 00:03:08,659
after a 2010 territorial dispute,

68
00:03:08,659 --> 00:03:11,409
which resulted in... a push by Japanese industry

69
00:03:11,409 --> 00:03:13,939
to develop substitutes and alternatives,

70
00:03:13,939 --> 00:03:16,849
ultimately hurting Chinese producers.”

71
00:03:16,849 --> 00:03:18,250
And then last year,

72
00:03:18,250 --> 00:03:20,470
Japan had a huge windfall,

73
00:03:20,470 --> 00:03:25,610
discovering enough rare earth minerals to
last 780 years.

74
